		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />O.k., yesterday, I played &quot;Castlevania (U) (PRG1)&quot; and guess what: It crashed as well. Not on the floor with the Grim Reaper, but when I went through the door that leads you to that small floor right before Frankenstein.<br /><br />It is definitely version PRG1. I know it because I opened the cartridge and checked it: &quot;NES-CV-1 PRG&quot; is written on the chip.<br /><br />So, what's with this bug? I always read that the bug from PRG0 was fixed in PRG1, but the game still crashes. How come that this specific crash isn't mentioned anywhere? Or is it a completely unrelated issue?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
