		<td><b>Re: &quot;Castlevania&quot; freezes</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well back when I used to play PAL NES hardware with the ZIF 72-pin connector, having a game crash because of the connector wasn't all that uncommon. With emulators and an imported Famicom, this doesn't happen any more. However, it might also have been a rare soft bug that wasn't fixed in PRG1, with an interrupt race condition or something.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


